    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA100-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu parattait talaivikkup pāṅkāyiṉār kēṭpa viṟalikku uṭampaṭac colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the other woman said to be in agreement with the dancing girl when those close to HER were listening.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA100">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uḷḷutoṟu nakuvēṉ ṟōḻi vaḷḷukir</l>
<l>            mārik kokkiṉ kūrala kaṉṉa</l>
<l>            kuṇṭunī rāmpaṟ ṟaṇṭuṟai yūraṉ</l>
<l>            ṟēṅkama ḻaimpāl paṟṟi yemvayiṉ</l>
<l>            vāṉkō lelvaḷai vauviya pūcal </l>
<l>            ciṉaviya mukattuc ciṉavātu ceṉṟuniṉ</l>
<l>            maṉaiyōṭ kuraippa leṉṟaliṉ muṉaiyūrp</l>
<l>            pallā neṭunirai villi ṉoyyun</l>
<l>            tērvaṇ malaiyaṉ muntaip pēricaip</l>
<l>            pulampuri vayiriyar nalampuri muḻaviṉ </l>
<l>            maṇṇār kaṇṇi ṉatiru</l>
<l>            naṉṉa rāḷa ṉaṭuṅkañar nilaiyē.</l>
    </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>I smile, friend, whenever I remember</l>
<l rend="indent">the state of shivering affliction in the good man,</l>
<l rend="indent">shaking like the eye full of earth of the drum</l>
<l rend="indent2">that does good for the dancers that perform on the field(?)<note place="foot">Do we have to read <term xml:lang="ta">pulam</term> in the sense of <term xml:lang="ta">kaḷam</term>, "dance floor"? Or is there an opportunity for dancers to be in the fields?</note></l>
<l rend="indent3">of great fame in front of generous Malaiyaṉ with the chariot,</l>
<l rend="indent3">who dragged along with [his] bow a long row of many cows</l>
<l rend="indent4">from the front village(?),</l>
<l rend="indent">when I said: “I will tell to her in your house,</l>
<l rend="indent2">going, without being angry, with an angry face,</l>
<l rend="indent2">of the fight where he snatched the light bangles in a pure row</l>
<l rend="indent3">on us, grasping our honey-scented five parts [of hair]”,</l>
<l rend="indent">the man from the village by the cool ghat</l>
<l rend="indent3">with white lotuses in the deep water,</l>
<l rend="indent2">like the sharp beaks of cranes in the shower, with sharp nails<note place="foot">Why <term xml:lang="ta">vaḷḷukir</term> for a <term xml:lang="ta">kokku</term> – what are the sharp nails of a crane?</note>.</l>
        </lg>
